yourself the author of my fate : How vast the change ! your Flora's now become The general pity , not the boast of Rome

you felt his agonising cares : Gross artifice , that this from him could move , And not from Flora , whom you say you love : You could not bear to hear your rival sigh , Yet bear unmoved to see your mistress die
Inhuman hypocrite ! nor thus can he My wrongs , and my distress , obdurate ,
